the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are George, your role in this game is villager.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAlicia's speech: Good morning, everyone. I have been observing the group closely and have some concerns about Andrew. I believe he may be a werewolf based on the information I have gathered. It is crucial that we keep a close eye on him and consider him a high priority for elimination. Additionally, I suggest that the Guard protect a key player tonight to ensure their safety. The Witch should also use her antidote wisely, as it is a valuable resource in our fight against the werewolves. Let us work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nAndrew's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to address Alicia's concerns about me. I understand that she has some suspicions, but I assure you that I am not a werewolf. I have been observing the group closely and have not seen any behavior that would suggest I am part of the werewolf faction. In fact, I believe that the Guard should focus on protecting the Seer, as they are a key player in our fight against the werewolves. The Witch should also use her antidote wisely, as it is a valuable resource. Let us work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nApril's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to thank Alic